sox
-------------------------------------------
SoX (also known as Sound eXchange) translates sound files between
different file formats, and optionally applies various sound effects.

SoX is intended as the Swiss Army knife of sound processing tools.  It
doesn't do anything very well, but sooner or later it comes in very
handy.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.21-2
  libgsm0-1.0.12-1
  libmad-0.15.1b-2
  libmp3lame0-3.96.1-1
  libogg0-1.1.2-1
  libvorbis0-1.1.1-1
  libvorbisenc2-1.1.1-1
  libvorbisfile3-1.1.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.21-2
  autoconf2.5-2.60-1
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.2.6-1
  gawk-3.1.5-2
  gcc-core-3.4.4-1
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-1

Canonical homepage:
  http://sox.sourceforge.net/

Canonical download:
  http://prdownloads.sourceforge.net/sox/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack sox-12.18.2-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./sox-12.18.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/sox-12.18.2-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/sox-12.18.2-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/bin/play
  /usr/bin/rec
  /usr/bin/sox.exe
  /usr/bin/soxmix.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/sox-12.18.2.README
  /usr/share/doc/sox-12.18.2/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/sox-12.18.2/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/sox-12.18.2/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/sox-12.18.2/README
  /usr/share/doc/sox-12.18.2/TODO
  /usr/share/man/man1/sox.1.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/soxexam.1.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/soxmix.1

